data.description:
You're looking for a new car. Of course you wan't to approach this in a systematic way. You have to implement the evaluateCars function which takes a list of cars and a criteria object as inputs. As a return, a list of all cars satifying the criterias is expected.

Conditions:
- The price should not exceed the maxPrice criteria
- The power-to-weight ratio is calculated as follows (horsepower/weight)
- The power-to-weight ratio of the car has to exceed that value from the criteria
- Multiple colors are allowed as criteria, the cars have to match one of the colors from the criteria
- Colors are not case-sensitive

Object definitions:

class Car{
  private String name;
  private String color;
  private int weight;
  private int horsepower;
  private int price;
}

class Criteria {
  String[] colors;
  float powerToWeightRatio;
  int maxPrice;
}

The attributes are private and have to be accessed using GETTER methods.
e.g. name -> getName, powerToWeightRatio -> getPowerToWeightRatio
